page.title: 06Principal Features
page.content: Bransgore is mainly flat.There are a few low hills to the east. There is very nice scenery.You can walk your dog on Gus common. There are lots of places where you can walk such as the lanes off Burley Road.There are two fords at Water Ditch where you can paddle.There are a few streams and quite a lot of wild flowers.Cows are in the farmer's fields.The New Forest is very near by.The lowest area is only ten feet above sea level and the highest point is just sixty feet above sea level.The land is good for pasture and arable crops.
